HEADWORD: Schema
<hw>Sche"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Schemata</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, E. <plw>Schemas</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[G. See <er>Scheme</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Kantian
Philos.)</fld> <def>An outline or image universally applicable to a
general conception, under which it is likely to be presented to the
mind; <as>as, five dots in a line are a <ex>schema</ex> of the number
five; a preceding and succeeding event are a <ex>schema</ex> of cause
and effect</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Schematic</ent>⟦br⟧
